<subSubSection id="469E0AC273594F37DCBE7182FB60FD21" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0E3B594973594F37DCBE7182FB60FD21" blockId="2.[151,1437,434,641]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">
This genus includes only the 
<typeStatus id="D13FE7EB73594F37DDF47182FA63FE6C" box="[477,525,434,460]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">type</typeStatus>
species. Within the family 
<taxonomicName id="C98422CA73594F37DF177182FBBCFE6C" authorityName="Gaud &amp; Atyeo" authorityYear="1978" box="[830,978,434,460]" class="Arachnida" family="Caudiferidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Caudiferidae</taxonomicName>
, this genus clearly differs from two other genera, 
<taxonomicName id="C98422CA73594F37DCD871E6FA15FE51" authority="Gaud &amp; Mouchet, 1959" authorityName="Gaud &amp; Mouchet" authorityYear="1959" box="[241,635,470,497]" class="Arachnida" family="Caudiferidae" genus="Caudifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3CF0855B73594F37DCD871E6F90DFE50" box="[241,355,470,496]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Caudifera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6A1524B873594F37DD4571E6FA15FE51" author="Gaud, J. &amp; Mouchet, J." box="[364,635,470,497]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" pagination="149 - 208" refId="ref6816" refString="Gaud, J. &amp; Mouchet, J. (1959) Acariens plumicoles (Analgesoidea) parasites des oiseaux du Cameroun III. Dermoglyphidae. Annales de Parasitologie humaine et comparee, 34, 149 - 208. https: // doi. org / 10.1051 / parasite / 1959341149" type="journal article" year="1959">Gaud &amp; Mouchet, 1959</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="3CF0855B73594F37DE9D71E6FB38FE50" box="[692,854,470,496]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Semicaudifera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6A1524B873594F37DF7671E6FC3EFE50" author="Gaud, J. &amp; Atyeo, W. T." box="[863,1104,470,496]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" pagination="1 - 193" refId="ref6753" refString="Gaud, J. &amp; Atyeo, W. T. (1996) Feather mites of the world (Acarina: Astigmata): The supraspecific taxa. Musee royal de l'Afrique centrale, Annales, Sciences zoologiques, 277 (Pt. 1 &amp; 2), 1 - 193 (text) &amp; 1 - 436 (illustrations)." type="journal article" year="1996">Gaud &amp; Atyeo, 1996</bibRefCitation>
, in having the following features. In males of 
<taxonomicName id="C98422CA73594F37DD4171CAFA7CFDB4" authorityName="Dubinin" authorityYear="1950" box="[360,530,506,532]" class="Arachnida" family="Caudiferidae" genus="Compressalges" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3CF0855B73594F37DD4171CAFA7CFDB4" box="[360,530,506,532]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Compressalges</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the opisthosoma is strongly narrowed posteriorly and with a pair of elongated opisthosomal lobes, the ventral side of opisthosoma has long epimerites IVa and adanal apodemes, and legs IV are hypertrophied; in females, the external copulatory tube is absent and the copulatory opening is situated terminally between setae 
<emphasis id="3CF0855B73594F37DD137256F90FFD20" box="[314,353,614,640]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">ps1</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="6A1524B873594F37DD597256FA61FD21" author="Dubinin, V. B." box="[368,527,614,641]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" pagination="537 - 540" refId="ref6333" refString="Dubinin, V. B. (1950) Features of the structures of the fastening apparatus of the feather mite Compressalges nipponiae V. Dubinin, gen. and sp. nov. Proceedings of the USSR Academy of Sciences, 70, 537 - 540. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1950">Dubinin 1950</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="6A1524B873594F37DE327256FB6CFD21" author="Gaud, J. &amp; Atyeo, W. T." box="[539,770,614,641]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" pagination="1 - 193" refId="ref6753" refString="Gaud, J. &amp; Atyeo, W. T. (1996) Feather mites of the world (Acarina: Astigmata): The supraspecific taxa. Musee royal de l'Afrique centrale, Annales, Sciences zoologiques, 277 (Pt. 1 &amp; 2), 1 - 193 (text) &amp; 1 - 436 (illustrations)." type="journal article" year="1996">Gaud &amp; Atyeo 1996</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
